# Battle of Baziaș (1460)

}}
The Battle of Baziaș also named the Battle of Pozazin was a military engagement which took place east of Smederevo in 1460. Ottoman forces commanded by Mihaloğlu Ali Bey defeated a Hungarian army lead by Michael Szilágyi. The Hungarian leader and many of his followers were captured and later excecuted on orders of Mehmed II.
